race.comment: BUSY FINGERS (3) bumped into one first-up at Geraldton when beaten 2.8L off the winner. He's sure to be better for that effort and now Pike hops in the saddle in a good push for his chances. Slightly up in trip looks a good move and with improvement expected, he can get the job done. LANFRANCO (12) stuck on well here first-up over 1100m when beaten 4L after being a touch slow into stride. The rise in trip looks ideal for him and he should be able to sit closer now up in distance. Can make his presence felt with improvement on the cards. PURE SILVER (15) was just fair last time in work, but they were both on Heavy rated surfaces. Back onto a good deck today with a nice trial under her belt and the blinkers on make her a very attractive proposition. ORDASHUS (1) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back to form. GIGI GOGO (14) is not out of this first-up.
